Give constant reproduction rate

Source: R/project_methods.R
constantRDD.Rd

Simply returns the value from species_params$constant_reproduction.

constantRDD(rdi, species_params, ...)

Arguments

rdi

Vector of density-independent reproduction rates \(R_p\) for all species.
species_params

A species parameter dataframe. Must contain a column constant_reproduction.
...

Unused

Value

Vector species_params$constant_reproduction

See also

Other functions calculating density-dependent reproduction rate: BevertonHoltRDD(), RickerRDD(), SheperdRDD(), noRDD()
